<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/Forum9/HTML/001299.html">
<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=0 WIDTH="95%"><TR ><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#F0DCA0" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Momaw</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Has anybody found a pattern or consistent time delay before the stores change their inventory?   It's very frustrating if you're looking to buy something, and nobody has it, and nobody seems to know when the next shipment of goods is coming in :P</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Harroine</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">in my experiences, the regular stores restock every 2 days or so, wandering traders (elves in Dark forest, dwarves in city, etc.) are less regular, i guess about 4 days or so.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">judee</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Is that all stores, even George's? I know George restocks on potions, but he sure seems to have the same inventory for a long time now. My warrior can't find a decent set of greaves - has none at the moment, and the best sword he has found is still a training sword, even though it does have a mana drain. Lol, yeah, right, he has exactly 30 mana, not exactly leaning in that direction!<P>He's stuck at the third level of the catacombs. Not enough armor, not enough weapon power, and not enough mana to use the one meteor spell he has effectively.<P>I think I'll do him over and wait do the reload thing til George has a good inventory for once! Because it seems once that inventory is set, it takes awhile to change, at least in aleroth.<P>judee<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ariana</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Judee - Playing hardcore (one death and I start over) I have build up a lot of experience with the early part of the game *grins*. You are correct about George's inventory - but there is a guaranteed way of getting through this part of the game fairly easily if you play a warrior. It takes advantage of the excellent bow always found on George's table.<P>I start the game by going straight there. If the bow is badly damaged I start over (getting it "new" is a convenience to avoid more frequent need to repair it). Otherwise I keep going. I get all of George's stuff from the outer room when he goes into the inner room (chain armor, the bow and odds and ends to sell) and do the normal start-of-game things, but even intending to be a melee fighter not an archer I put all my points into agility until getting it to 30. I can now use the bow.<P>The bow is good enough to let me kill anything around outside of the catacombs without serious difficulty unless I am careless - the two Jakes and the strong orcs included. By level 8 or so I have two choices. Clear out the catacombs (still using the bow) or head to the main part of the map and go shopping in the marketplace there for better stuff. Meanwhile I am raising strength so I can use the better melee weapons I will get there. Until getting a good bastard sword or claymore I stick with the bow - unlike some CRPGs a bow works fine for hand-to-hand combat in DD. <P>You need to be a bit careful in the catacombs or a skeleton lord or conjurer or master conjurer or even guardian can kill you, but if you move around and don't try to be too cheap with potions (and use restoration frequently) you can get through easily enough at levels 5-8 with the bow.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cronus</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Share my observation on shop re-stock timing/pattern.<BR>I notice in my game, Arc Magincia, General store re-stock every day while the magic store re-stock every 2-3 days. Tingalf re-stock every 1/2 day.<BR>For general store and magic store, I often sell my loots to them such that it drains out all their cash. I do believe that helps to trigger the re-stock at a fast pace.<BR>As for Tingalf, he seems to re-stock automatically... I always buy lockpicks from him and within 1/2 day, he have lockpicks for sell again ! I didn't have to drain his cash(gold).<BR>Hope to get more feedback from the other players.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Stabbey_the_Clown</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The higher your level, the less exp you will get from the monsters in the Catacombs.<P>Exp/kill is based on your Clvl and the monsters HP.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</IFRAME>
</FONT>
